# This repo is the SOURCING ENGINE only: generic rules + public job data.
# Everything below stays local and is never committed.

# Local working files (not part of the engine)
CLAUDE.md
pipeline.db
output/
daily/
archive/
portfolio/
templates/
ops/
# scripts/generate_resume_variants.py — un-ignored 2026-06-01: Phase 2 extends
# this into a committed module (resume-variant derivation from an uploaded
# resume) that the runtime intake path imports. Leaving it ignored shipped a
# tree whose committed code imported an uncommitted module.
scripts/generate_daily.py
scripts/ingest_listing.py
scripts/init_db.py

# Secrets
.env
.env.*
email.env
*.key
*.pem
secrets.*

# Junk
.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
feedback/

# Working outputs (per-role/per-application files; never committed)
applications/
targets/*

# macOS cloud-sync conflict ghosts (handled in Phase 0 C0; never commit duplicates)
* 2.md
* 2.py
* 3.py
* 2.db-journal

# Beads / Dolt files (added by bd init)
.dolt/
*.db
.beads-credential-key

# Deploy-guard runtime state (PID + startup commit snapshot — regenerated on each daemon start)
state/deploy-guard-startup.json
state/deploy-guard-notified.flag

# Runtime logs (regenerated by the daemon; never durable)
state/*.log
state/*.err
state/observability/

# Runtime PID files (e.g. state/phoenix.pid — written by phoenix_capture.sh on start)
state/*.pid

# Per-user profile drafts/confirmed profiles (Phase 2 intake — contains
# resume-derived PII; per-user runtime data, never repo content). The Supabase
# per-user table (Phase D/0) is the eventual home; this is the local seam.
state/profiles/

# Tracked exceptions inside targets/ (everything else in targets/* stays local):
#   *_seed.json  — curated seed data (human-maintained input)
#   *_boards.json — generated board lists (weekly discovery output)
#   discovered_slugs.json — harvest output (ATS slugs from local .md files;
#     .md files stay gitignored as personal research; this JSON is the minimal
#     coverage data the production run needs on a fresh checkout so _harvest_targets()
#     returns Formic etc. even when no .md files are present)
!targets/vc_seed.json
!targets/vc_boards.json
!targets/yc_boards.json
!targets/discovered_slugs.json
templates/.backup_*/
state/ledger_backup*.json
state/grounding_flags_fallback.jsonl
*.egg-info/
